          <p class="bio">Sylvie Shrum is a psychology student pursuing a BA and MA through the accelerated 5-year program at <a href="https://www.newschool.edu/lang/">Eugene Lang College of Liberal Arts</a> and the <a href="https://www.newschool.edu/nssr/">New School for Social Research</a>. Her work centers an interdisciplinary approach to social research that is informed by sociology, anthropology, political science, and psychology, with a particular interest in social psychology and technology studies. She is deeply passionate about the connection between social justice research and practice, with plans to pursue a PhD in psychology after completing the MA program.</p>
